<p><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;2.2 Non Delivery of Ticket :</b></p>
<p>If the courier is unable to deliver the ticket – due to nobody being available at the address or proof of identity as indicated above not being produced in original – a card indicating the address and phone number of the courier’s office will be left at the destination address. The customer is required to call the courier and advise when a delivery should be made. The customer can also choose to go over to the courier’s office, with suitable proof of identity in original and can collect the ticket personally. </p>
     <p>If after three attempts by the courier and subsequent attempts to contact the customer by IRCTC , the ticket cannot be delivered, it will be returned to IRCTC and it will be customer’s responsibility to collect it from IRCTC’s office producing necessary proof of identity. IRCTC will not be responsible for any loss, damage, inconvenience etc. on this account. </p> 


<p><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;2.3 Non-authorization of payment</b> more than once by payment gateway for tickets booked by you is liable to result in deregistration of your account with this site, without any notice.</p> 

<p><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;2.4 Charges You are required to pay</b> the cost of the ticket and the service charge (including Service Tax) as indicated in the reservation page through any one of the payment options provided on the page.</p> 
<p>For I-Ticket service charge at Rs. 80/-per ticket plus service tax  (not per passenger) for Sleeper Class/Second class and Rs 120/- per ticket plus service tax (not per passenger) for higher classes will be levied.</p> 
<p>For E-Ticket IRCTC service charges is Rs.20/- plus service tax (second / sleeper) and Rs.40/- plus service tax  for higher class. Service charge levied is not refundable. Further the transaction charges as indicated on the payment page will be levied by the bankers. Difference of fare if any due later, consequent to revision in tariffs etc. shall have to be paid by you at the station before commencement of your journey.</p> 
<p>For booking through mobile phones, the operators charge differently. Please confirm from your mobile operator these details before attempting to book tickets through your handsets.    </p>  


<p><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;2.5 After booking the tickets </b>through this site, the details of berth/seat number, RAC/Waitlist position at the time of booking, PNR No and a unique Transaction ID will appear on your screen. You must preserve the Transaction ID and all other details for future reference.  </p>  
<p><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;2.6 CANCELLATION/REFUND/MODIFICATION OF TICKETS I-tickets Cancellation:</b> For I-tickets, cancellation is not possible on the Internet. To cancel a ticket, the customer will have to submit the ticket at a PRS counter. The fare paid by the customer will be refunded electronically (as credit to the relevant credit card / account used for the transaction) after deducting cancellation charges. Bank charges that are being levied by the Payment Gateways/Banks are not subject to refund in the event of cancellation of tickets by the Customer. The cancellation charge is determined by the Indian Railway's rules for cancellation and is based on the time of cancellation and the status of the ticket. The service charge is not refunded.PRS counter will issue a cancellation ticket/receipt and IRCTC will credit the amount of refund due, to the customer's account. No cash refund will be given to the passenger.</p>   <p>For details please refer to the Indian Railways' rules 
 for Cancellation. </p>
