<p><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;2.7 Cancellation of I-tickets </b>can be done on all PRS counters from 08.00 A.M. to 8:00 P.M. on weekdays and from 08.00 A.M. to 2.00 P.M. on Sundays. On closure of PRS counters at 8.00 P.M on weekdays and at 02.00 P.M. on Sundays, the passenger may approach for cancellation at refund terminals provided at certain stations.</p>
<p>Such cancellations through the refund terminals are allowed only for tickets available for travel on the same day and up to 12 hrs on the following day. I-Tickets can also be cancelled at the boarding station, within 6 hours before the scheduled departure of the train and upto two hours irrespective of distance.</p>
<p>In case refund terminals are not available due to any reason, to cancel such tickets, the passenger may get his ticket cancelled manually through the stationmaster and get Ticket Deposit Receipt (TDR) and apply for refund to IRCTC. The application should be addressed to, <BR>

General Manager (Operations), <BR>
Indian Railway Catering and Tourism Corporation Ltd.<br>
1stFloor, Internet Ticketing Centre<br>
IRCA Building, State Entry Road,<br>
New Delhi - 110055<br></p>
<p><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;2.8 In the case of night trains</b> leaving between 09.00 P.M. and 06.00 A.M. (actual departure) I-tickets can be cancelled at PRS counters within the time limit specified in the cancellation rules or within four hours after the opening of reservation office on the following day whichever is later. </p> 
<p><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;2.9 REFUND IN FAILED TRANSACTIONS / CANCELLED TICKETS: </b> Though IRCTC's payment reconciliation team works on a 24 x 7 basis, IRCTC offers no guarantees whatsoever for the accuracy or timeliness of the refunds reaching the Customers card/bank accounts. This is on account of the multiplicity of organizations involved in processing of online transactions, the problems with Internet infrastructure currently available and working days/holidays of financial institutions. On line Cancellation of I-tickets is not provided through Internet. For cancellation/partial cancellations, the journey ticket is to be presented to the nearest Railway reservation office along with a requisition for cancellation/partial cancellation. The ticket is cancelled, partly cancelled by the Railways but no cash refund is permitted against such tickets. The Railways send a refund file to IRCTC on the next day with respect to the above type of transactions (Fare less the cancellation cha
 rges as per extent railway rules) and the refund amount received from the Railways is credited to the customer's account electronically. E-tickets however can be cancelled on line up to preparation of the chart.</p>
     <p> To get the refund quickly, customers are advised to cancel their tickets within the prescribed time limits, wherever possible. In cases where the tickets are not cancelled within the prescribed time limits, the customers should deposit their I-Tickets with the nearest station master and get a ticket deposit receipt (TDR) and send the same in original to IRCTC for condoning the delay for cancellation of tickets. In case a passenger faces any problem in cancelling an E-Ticket online, He should apply for cancellation by sending the E-ticket details through email to etickets@irctc.co.in. IRCTC will process such cases with the Railways for grant of the due refund on behalf of the customer. The time taken and amount of refund granted in such cases is dependent on the merit of each case and is to be decided by the Railways and IRCTC not responsible for delays at the railway end in any such case. Amount of refund whenever received from the Railways shall be credited to the c
 u stomer's account immediately.</p>
 
