<tr> 
				<td class="borderB" height="25" align="left" colspan="2"><a name="Q4"><h3>Mumbai Suburban Season Ticket Terms & Conditions  <h3></td>
             </tr>


<tr>
<td colspan="2">
<div class="content_numeric" align="left">
<ul>


<li><b><a href="#1">Services Offered</a></b></li>  
 <li><b> <a href="#2">Services NOT Offered </a> </b></li>  
 <li><b><a href="#3"> Dispatch and delivery of tickets </a> </b></li>  
 <li><b><a href="#4"> Charges  </a></b></li>  
<li><b><a href="#5"> Use of tickets  </a></b></li>  
 <li><b><a href="#6"> Others  </a></b></li> 
 
<p>The IRCTC provides the facility for transacting with Mumbai suburban season ticket System through the Internet. All Rules and regulations pertaining to Mumbai suburban season ticket booking will apply to all such transactions along with special conditions imposed for Internet based booking.</p>

<a name="1"><p><b>Services Offered</b></p>  
<p>Online Booking facility of Mumbai suburban season ticket for registered users who agree to the terms and conditions set forth in this document. </p>
 
<p> Booking through Internet is allowed from 03:00 AM to 11:00 PM (Indian Standard Time) on all days including Sundays. Service hours are liable to be changed without prior notice. </p>
 
<p>Season Ticket Booking is allowed against adult quota only. </p>
 
<p>Registered users will be able to purchase a season ticket from 2 days up to 10 days in advance of the date of booking. </p>
 
<p> For season tickets to be delivered by courier to the customer there must be two clear calendar days between the booking date and the date of travel. , e.g. on 1st you can book season ticket valid from 4th (2 clear days) up to 10th.<!--  For details of areas covered, please <a href='../Deliverypopup.html' target='_blank'>Click here</a> --></p>
 
 
<a name="2"><p><b>Services NOT Offered  </b></p> 
<p> Concessional season tickets booked through Internet. </p>
 
<p> CANCELLATION/REFUND/MODIFICATION OF TICKETS -For MUMBAI suburban season tickets booked through internet, no cancellations/refund/modification will be permitted on the Internet or through counter. </p>
 
<p>Season ticket booking for child ticket. </p>
 
<p> Student concession. </p>
 
<p> Modification and Cancellation of season tickets </p>
 
<p>  Issue of duplicate tickets for lost, mutilated or torn season tickets. </p>
 
<p> Change of source station and destination stations of season tickets . </p>
 
<p> Personal Collection of tickets by customers from any designated centers.  </p>

<a name="3"><p><b>Dispatch and delivery of tickets  </b></p> 
<p> Tickets will be delivered to the customer at his desired address through courier. This delivery of season tickets through courier is limited to postal addresses covered by the pin codes listed under the link "Places of Delivery ". This delivery of season Tickets through courier is limited to the following places. </p>
1. Mumbai<BR>
2. Nashik <BR>
3. Pune <BR>
4. Surat <BR>
5. Thane <BR>
 
<p>  Proof of Identity: We will only release possession of the ticket to the registered user on production of proof of identity in original (Passport / Voter photo identity card issued by Election Commission of India / Driving Licence issued by RTO / Pan Card issued by Income Tax Department / Photo Identity card having serial number issued by Central / State Government / Student Identity Card with photograph issued by recognized School/College for their students / Nationalized Bank Passbook with photographs / Credit Cards issued by Banks with laminated photograph /Unique Identification Card "Aadhaar” / Photo identity cards having serial number issued by public sector Undertakings of State/Central Government, District Administrations, Municipal bodies and Panchayat Administrations will be accepted as proof of identity for undertaking journey under Tatkal scheme only if the passenger whose photograph is available on the ration card is travelling) If the registered user cannot b
 e present to receive the ticket, the ticket can be delivered to any person authorized by him (on production of a signed authorization from the user indicating the transaction ID and identification as listed above). If either of the above is not possible, the ticket will not be delivered but will be retained by IRCTC. IRCTC will not be responsible for any loss or damage or inconvenience to the customer on the above account. </p>
 
<p> Dispatch of Tickets: Once you have done your booking and the transaction is successful, the ticket will be dispatched to the address provided in the Ticket Booking page. For the present, delivery of tickets is limited to postal addresses covered by the pin codes listed under the link "Places of Delivery ".This delivery of season Tickets through courier is limited to the following places.</p>
1. Mumbai<BR>
2. Nashik <BR>
3. Pune <BR>
4. Surat <BR>
5. Thane <BR>
 
<p>  Non Delivery of Ticket: If the courier is unable to deliver the ticket - due to nobody being available at the address or proof of identity as indicated above not being produced in original - a card indicating the address and phone number of the courier’s office will be left at the destination address. The customer is required to call the courier and advise when the delivery should be made. The customer can also choose to go over to the courier’s office, with suitable proof of identity in original and can collect the ticket personally. </p>
 
<p>If after three attempts by the courier and subsequent attempts to contact the customer by IRCTC, the ticket cannot be delivered, it will be returned to IRCTC and it will be customer’s responsibility to collect it from IRCTC’s office producing necessary proof of identity. IRCTC will not be responsible for any loss, damage, inconvenience etc. on this account. </p>
 
 
<a name="4"><p><b> Charges   </b></p> 
<p> Services charges Nil for all classes </p> 
<p> Refund failed: Though IRCTC's payment reconciliation team works on a 24 x 7 basis, IRCTC offers no guarantees whatsoever for the accuracy or timeliness of the refunds reaching the Customers card/bank accounts. This is on account of the multiplicity of organizations involved in processing of online transactions, the problems with Internet infrastructure currently available and working days/holidays of financial institutions. </p> 

<a name="5"><p><b> Use of Tickets   </b></p> 
<p> You must check your ticket for errors, if any, as soon as you receive it. If an error is noticed and the ticket does not comply with the information set out in the reservation page, Do contact us at 24X7 Hrs. Customer Support at 011-39340000.
 </p>
 

<a name="6"><p><b>Others   </b></p> 
<p>  Every season ticket will have the Identity card number printed in it. If the Identity card printed on the Season ticket of the passenger does not match with original Identity card, passenger will be treated as passenger traveling without tickets and dealt with accordingly. It is requested to take at most care while filling the Identity card numbers during booking your tickets. Cancellation of season tickets is not permitted and IRCTC will not be responsible for any loss or damage or inconvenience to the customer on the above account. </p>
 
<p>  Season ticket issued through Internet are valid only along with ,the identity card issued by the railway with photograph of the holder duly pasted on the Identity card .Passenger found traveling on season tickets without Identity card will be treated as passengers travelling without tickets and dealt with accordingly. </p>
 
<p> After pressing the “Buy” button, if the “Ticket reservation confirmation page” is not displayed on your monitor due to power failure or Internet link /communication failure, please click the “Transaction History” menu on the left side of the screen. This page will display as highlighted those cases whose booking status we have not received due to communication problem along with other successful booking details. </p>
<p> User can click the "Update ticket status" option available in Transaction History Page to know the status of the ticket .If ticket status is booked You will be displayed the ticket details along with confirmation message. If ticket not booked user can retry booking by clicking the "Book my Season ticket" link on the left side of the screen. You are also advised to check your e-mail or contact IRCTC, if necessary. </p>
<p> It may be noted that one user can have only one userid .If you have more than one userid ,IRCTC reserve the right to cancel any or both userid. For customers who book tickets with more than one user id, IRCTC will not be responsible for any loss/damage or inconvenience to the customer  </p>
<p>  Who can I ask if I have additional questions? : Feel free to contact us any time and we'll answer any additional questions you may have. Call us at Delhi 011-39340000  24*7 Hrs Our email address is seasontickets@irctc.co.in </p>
